header.gameNote: SHAMROCK OFFICE SOLUTIONS CLASSIC AT MORAGA CA

article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 64, Binghamton 43
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- Eddie Williams scored 14 points and Stephen F. Austin defeated Binghamton 64-43 Wednesday night in the Shamrock Office Solutions Classic. Jereal Scott had 12 points for the Lumberjacks (9-3), while Walt Harris had 10. Stephen F. Austin shot 50 percent from the field in the game and built a 30-point lead in the second half. Chrietien Lukasa led all scorers with 18 points for Binghamton (4-10). The Bearcats only led after scoring the game's first basket and were down by double digits less than seven minutes into the contest. The Lumberjacks led 37-21 at halftime.
